   An earthquake of magnitude 7.7 hit northwestern Iran on June 21, 1990 killing at least 50,000 people
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   and leaving 400,000 homeless.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The quake occurred when most people were inside asleep and hit a coastal floodplain
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   where loosely deposited soil shifts easily and caused the fragile adobe homes in the area to collapse.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
